{% block description %}
<p>Since 25 February 2012, Spotify's users have been asking for song changes
to show up in the OS X Notification center in <a
    href="https://community.spotify.com/t5/Live-Ideas/OS-X-Notification-Center/idi-p/111050">a suggestion
</a> which has garnered 400+ votes.</p>
<p>On April 06 2013 I put together a small OS X application which implemented
that functionality. It did one thing and it did it well. The first release was a
whopping 70 lines (including comments!) and was contained in
<code>AppDelegate.h</code> and <code>AppDelegate.m</code>.</p>
<p>The next day it was featured in <a href="http://thenextweb.com/apps/2013/04/07/this-simple-app-brings-spotify-to-your-macs-notification-center/">TheNextWeb</a>.</p>
<p>Since then, through new features and bug fixes, it's ballooned to 561 lines
(plus third-party libraries!) while trying to stay to true to "less is better."</p>
